<Class name="JtdGenerationHelper" id="2f89ccb6-a369-44d4-aef4-43a05fa01f39">
    <superclass name="Object"/>
    <transient/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <abstract/>
    <text>

Create a new subclass for each different type of transaction (or chain of transactions) that is to be created.
The main logic will get called for the number of times that are specified in the jtdController profile editor.


To Setup a new transaction

1. Create new subclass under CMITransactionLoader
2. CMIReadTransaction/CMIUpdateTransaction - create a new startup&lt;Transaction&gt; method and make sure it creates the new subclass .
         Create a main&lt;transaction&gt; if you need to do something special. eg. read file to get data.
          
3. New subclass - reimplement  selectStartupForm  . This usually selects the form to be used.
4. New subclass - reimplement 'main' 

Profile editor - this displays the method on CMIReadTransactiona dn CMIUpdateTransaction
   
				             SELECT    
       prolog       		  startup&lt;transaction&gt;    created above
       epilog                 closedown
       main                   defaultMain			 or   or main&lt;Transaction&gt; if you wanted something different</text>
    <DbClassMap file="Jtd"/>
    <PrimAttribute name="repeatable" id="5a38a9fe-cf02-4200-b5d0-3ef82a3343d2">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Boolean"/>
    </PrimAttribute>
</Class>
